RISC-V CPU
---

A 64-bit RISC V CPU written in python to teach myself risc architecture.

The goal is to be able to run https://github.com/mit-pdos/xv6-riscv - a minimal Unix-like full OS

NOTE: the project is not finished yet

Resourced I used
---

- https://book.rvemu.app/hardware-components/01-cpu.html
- https://www.eecs.yorku.ca/course_archive/2019-20/F/2021S/REF/RISCV-GreenCard.pdf


Implemented Instructions
---

- addi, addiw I ADD Immediate (Word) R[rd] = R[rs1] + imm
- add, addw R ADD (Word) R[rd] = R[rs1] + R[rs2]